{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_20","type":"reasoning","text":"**Planning test implementation**\n\nI'm thinking about how to create many tests with a pure Python reimplementation style. It seems we should add a new test file for U32Pair, perhaps following a similar pattern to the U8Pair and BoolPair tests. I'll need to inspect the existing pair tests for their style and how they format the command output string. That might help ensure consistency across the test files."}}
